                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Leahy, William D./102: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-27T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 27, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 28—4 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>621. I called on the Marshal this afternoon to take my leave. Our interview was
                    of the most cordial nature. The Marshal professed his sincere devotion for the
                    United States and expressed a hope that there will be no change in our friendly
                    relations.</p>
                <p>He said that while it might be necessary for France to continue to furnish
                    economic aid to Germany, France would never provide Germany with armed
                    assistance. He felt certain that Laval whom he described as being nearer to the
                    Germans than himself would also refuse to give military aid to Germany.</p>
                <p>During our conversation the Marshal remarked that at times such as these matters
                    which affect Franco-American relationships can be spoken of freely but should
                    not be made a matter of record.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
